-- Key facts about Hershey's new directors
-- 
-- Sun Nov 11, 2007 8:02pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/11/12/us-hershey-board-factbox-idUSN1142616320071112

 

 (Reuters) - Hershey Co ( HSY.N ) replaced eight members of its board of directors, the latest in a string of management shake-ups at the U.S. chocolate maker. 

 Following are highlights from the new directors' biographies: CHARLES A. DAVIS: Davis was head of Investment Banking Services and served on the International Executive Committee for Goldman, Sachs & Co, where he spent 23 years. He is the current chairman and chief executive of Stone Point Capital. EDWARD J. KELLY: Kelly is managing director of private equity firm The Carlyle Group. He is the former chairman, president and chief officer of Mercantile Bankshares Corporation. ARNOLD G. LANGBO: Langbo is the former chairman and chief officer of the Kellogg Company, where he worked for 44 years. He is a director of the Johnson & Johnson Company, Weyerhaeuser Company and the Whirlpool Corporation. JAMES E. NEVELS: Nevels is chairman of the minority-owned investment-advisory firm, The Swarthmore Group. He is also a board member of the Hershey Trust Company. THOMAS J. RIDGE: Ridge is president and chief officer at consulting company Ridge Global LLC. He is the former governor of Pennsylvania and the first Secretary of the U.S. Department of Homeland Security. CHARLES B. STRAUSS: Strauss is the former chairman and chief executive of Unilever North America. He is also a director of The Hartford Financial Services Group. KENNETH L. WOLFE: Wolfe spent 34 years with Hershey, serving, at various points, as its chief financial officer, president, chairman and chief executive. He also serves on the board of the Fidelity Family of Mutual Funds. LEROY S. ZIMMERMAN: Zimmerman is chairman of the board of the Hershey Trust Company. He was Pennsylvania's first elected attorney general and former chairman of Eckert Seamans Cherin & Mellot, LLC, where he currently works as senior counsel. (Reporting by Dana Ford)